[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The challenge implemented multiple XSS filters that could each be bypassed:                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Tag filtering removed first character of dangerous tags - bypass not needed since event handlers work                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. The key insight was that `alert("XSS")` with the literal string was being filtered, causing `alert()` to fire with `undefined`                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. String concatenation `"X"+"SS"` bypassed the filter while still producing the required alert message                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. The `autofocus` attribute ensures the XSS fires without user interaction                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. Breaking out of the `value` attribute context was straightforward with `"` since no escaping was applied                                          [32m│[0m
